vectorData.altText: That's right! Hepatocytes radiate outward from the central vein in a spoke-like fashion, they constitute the majority of the liver parenchyma.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

CV – Central vein, large venule found at center of liver lobule
H – Hepatocytes, radiate outward from the CV
S – Sinusoids, lined by endothelium, found between hepatocytes
